Description: Today I learned a lot about C# and MongoDB. The process of creating your own social networking application is very exciting!
We all look for inspiration in different things, today for me it was evening tea and a new episode of my favorite TV series.
I have completed my first C# project! It feels incredible! I learned so much about object-oriented programming and working with databases.
I need some advice! What is the best way to organize a data structure in MongoDB for a large project? I would be grateful for any advice or resources.
I found an interesting article about query optimization in MongoDB. If anyone else works with MongoDB, I can share the link.
